# High-Level System Architecture

This outlines the high-level architecture of your **HirePrep AI** platform. You can visualize this directly using **Mermaid diagrams**. 

> [!TIP]
> If you want to build or view architectures inside your editor, I highly recommend installing the VS Code extension **"Mermaid Markdown Syntax Highlighting"** combined with **"Markdown Preview Mermaid Support"** or the **"Draw.io Integration"** extension.

## Architecture Diagram
Here is how your MERN stack + AI project is structured:

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Define Styles
    classDef frontend fill:#0f172a,stroke:#10b981,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff;
    classDef backend fill:#1e293b,stroke:#3b82f6,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff;
    classDef database fill:#022c22,stroke:#10b981,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff;
    classDef external fill:#4c1d95,stroke:#a855f7,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff;

    %% Nodes
    subgraph Client ["Client Side (Frontend)"]
        UI["React UI (Vite)"]:::frontend
        Router["React Router v7"]:::frontend
        Axios["Axios (HTTP Client)"]:::frontend
        SCSS["Glassmorphism SCSS"]:::frontend
        UI --- Router
        UI --- SCSS
        Router --> Axios
    end

    subgraph Server ["Server Side (Backend Node.js)"]
        API["Express REST API"]:::backend
        Auth["JWT Authentication & bcrypt"]:::backend
        Upload["Multer (File Uploads)"]:::backend
        Parser["PDF-Parse (Extraction)"]:::backend
        GenAIService["AI Service (Zod Parsing)"]:::backend

        API --> Auth
        API --> Upload
        Upload --> Parser
        Parser --> GenAIService
    end

    subgraph Data ["Data Layer"]
        DB[(MongoDB via Mongoose)]:::database
    end

    subgraph External ["External Services"]
        LLM["Google Generative AI (Gemini)"]:::external
    end

    %% Connections
    Axios -- "HTTP Requests (JSON/FormData)" --> API
    GenAIService -- "Prompt & Context Sent" --> LLM
    LLM -- "Structured JSON Reply" --> GenAIService
    API -- "Read/Write Users & Reports" --> DB
```

### Component Breakdown

1. **Client Tier (Frontend)**
   - **React/Vite**: Renders the dynamic UI (Landing Page, Dashboard, Interview Roadmap).
   - **Axios**: Sends requests to the backend (including `multipart/form-data` for PDF uploads).
   - **State Management**: React Context (`AuthProvider`, `InterviewProvider`) handles global state.

2. **Application Tier (Backend API)**
   - **Express Framework**: Exposes REST endpoints (`/api/auth`, `/api/interviews`).
   - **File Processing**: `multer` intercepts incoming resumes, and `pdf-parse` extracts the raw text.
   - **AI Orchestration**: The [ai.service.js](file:///c:/Users/Harshit/Desktop/RESUME%20PROJECTS/interview-ai-yt-main/Backend/src/services/ai.service.js) compiles the extracted resume text, job description, and a strictly verified `Zod` schema into a prompt for the AI.

3. **Database Tier (MongoDB)**
   - **Mongoose Models**: 
     - **User Model**: Stores emails, hashed passwords (`bcrypt`), and profile details.
     - **Report Model**: Stores the structured interview strategies generated by the AI so users can refer back to them.

4. **External Services Tier**
   - **Google GenAI API**: Does the heavy lifting of reading the job description and resume, using Natural Language Processing to generate customized behavioral/technical questions and study roadmaps.
